00:00:02.742 --> 00:00:05.748
Hello boys and girls, this is Aunt Frenita

00:00:05.760 --> 00:00:11.645
and I have a wonderful story for you called 'A Child Like Me' 

00:00:12.034 --> 00:00:17.097
Today's memory verse is from Luke 2:51 

00:00:17.600 --> 00:00:22.468
It says 'Then He went down to Nazareth...and was obedient'

00:00:22.868 --> 00:00:28.960
 The message for today's story is 'we are like Jesus when we obey and help' 

00:00:29.748 --> 00:00:31.794
How do you show someone you love them?

00:00:32.765 --> 00:00:34.537
Do you give them lots of hugs?

00:00:35.371 --> 00:00:36.731
Are you kind to them?

00:00:37.680 --> 00:00:39.360
Do you give them presents?

00:00:40.331 --> 00:00:42.148
Do you do what they ask of you?

00:00:43.017 --> 00:00:45.291
Jesus was little just like you 

00:00:45.817 --> 00:00:50.251
He didn't go to nursery school. He stayed home with his mother, Mary 

00:00:50.834 --> 00:00:53.942
Everyday, she taught him about God

00:00:54.560 --> 00:00:57.965
She told him stories about Adam and Eve

00:00:58.434 --> 00:01:02.114
Noah and the Ark, David and Goliath 

00:01:02.685 --> 00:01:04.571
She taught Him how to pray 

00:01:04.970 --> 00:01:10.300
'Dear Heavenly Father, thank you for loving me! Amen' 

00:01:10.300 --> 00:01:10.502
Mary, His mother, taught Jesus songs about God, like the ones you learn in Sabbath School
